<SECOND>AM-Bank Robbery, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0800,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Band Director Arrested in Bank Robbery</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf, `Donald Hershberger ..., to CORRECT spelling
of detective Dunlap, sted Dunlop.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOUTH CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school band director was
arrested during a bank robbery Thursday and confessed to four other
holdups in West Virginia, city police said.
   Donald Hershberger, band leader at George Washington High School
in Charleston, was charged with one count each of aggravated robbery
and kidnapping after attempting to rob the Second Avenue Bank,
Detective David Dunlap said.
   School board member Wayne Crowder called the situation ``tragic
for the school system and for the man.''
   Police were called to the bank shortly before noon when bank
employees recognized Hershberger from photographs distributed after
the previous robberies, said Brenda Robertson, the bank's president.
   After his arrest, Hershberger confessed to robbing two banks in
Charleston, one in Buckhannon, and one in Bridgeport, Dunlop said.
   Hershberger, who police said was carrying a small-caliber pistol,
is being held without bond in the Kanawha County Jail. A hearing was
scheduled for Sept. 15.
</TEXT>
