<HEAD>Israeli Defense Minister Holds Talks With Senior U.S. Officials</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Rabin is
meeting today with senior Bush administration officials on the
stalled Mideast peace process and Palestinian unrest on the West
Bank and in Gaza.
   Rabin's talks with Defense Secretary Dick Cheney, National
Security Adviser Brent Scowcroft and Secretary of State James A.
Baker III kick off a series of visits by Israeli officials.
   He will be followed by Deputy Foreign Minister Benjamin
