<FIRST>r a PM-GumbyTribute     09-08 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gumby Tribute,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Texas Polka Band Joins Tribute to Small, Green TV Star</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Texas polka band has turned down Tracey Ullman,
but didn't hesitate when Gumby called.
   Brave Combo, a band from Denton that plays a mix of polka-tinged
music, was asked to contribute to Disney's ``The Gumby Project'' and
has sent back two songs.
   Band member Carl Finch said musicians were asked ``to write songs
about the Gumby experience.''
   Brave Combo penned songs called ``Pokey's Polka'' and ``Zydeco
Gumby Ya-Ya.''
   The Dallas Morning News reported that recording artists paying
tribute to the green rubber TV star will include Frank Sinatra Jr.,
Jonathan Richman, former Turtles Flo and Eddie, and reggae-rockers
Sly and Robbie. The record could be out as early as next month, the
newspaper said.
   Brave Combo members said they quickly turned down an invitation
to appear on ``The Tracey Ullman Show'' after learning they were to
appear in a sketch that parodied polka. Finch told the newspaper the
band's fans don't find polka a joking matter.
   ``They trust us,'' Finche said. ``They still trust that we love
the music.''
</TEXT>
