<FIRST>r i PM-Obit-Nkoane     09-08 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Obit-Nkoane,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Simeon Nkoane, Anti-Apartheid Bishop, Dies of Cancer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anglican Bishop Simeon Nkoane,
a dedicated anti-apartheid activist and colleague of Archbishop
Desmond Tutu, has died of cancer. He was 60.
   Nkoane, who died Thursday at his home in the black township of
KwaThema, was assistant bishop of the diocese directly east of
Johannesburg. He had been ill for several years.
   He was deeply involved in community affairs of black townships in
the Johannesburg area and officiated at many funerals of blacks
killed in political unrest.
   Nkoane was consecrated a bishop in 1982. Before that, he was dean
of St. Mary's Cathedral in central Johannesburg for five years.
</TEXT>
