<HEAD>Two Students Killed in Clashes Between Rival Groups</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rival groups of students clashed in two
cities, and at least two students were killed and 50 were injured,
police said Friday.
   The clashes took place Thursday in Comilla, 55 miles east of
Dhaka, and in Sailakupa, 80 miles west of the capital.
   Police said an unidentified college student was killed when a
bomb exploded during a clash between members of the Islamic
Students' Forum and the Nationalist Students' Party fighting for the
same rally site in Comilla.
