<HEAD>Nine Die From Food Poisoning</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least nine children died from food
poisoning after eating biscuits produced by the same factory, and 10
children were hospitalized after eating the biscuits, a report said
Friday.
   The newspaper Kompas said seven children in South Sumatra and two
in the neighboring province of Jambi died Wednesday.
   Police arrested two distributors of the biscuits and ordered the
factory that produces them closed, the newspaper said.
   Ahmad Azof, head of the South Sumatra Health Office, told the
newspaper the poisoning was caused by too much sodium nitrate, a
preservative, in the biscuits.
