<FIRST>r a AM-TeenSex     09-08 0281</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Teen Sex,0290</SECOND>
<HEAD>17-Year-Old Sentenced To 8 Years For Having Sex With 11-Year-Old</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-year-old has been sentenced to
eight years in prison for having sex with an 11-year-old girl who
became pregnant with twins.
   It took jurors only 20 minutes Thursday to find Carlos Johnson
guilty of sexual battery of a child under 12.
   Johnson was 16 in August 1988 when he and the girl had sex at the
Walker Ford Community Center. In January the girl delivered twins
born four months early. One was stillborn, the other soon died.
   ``It's true kids have sex with kids all the time. But maybe once
they see this, it'll stop,'' Assistant State Attorney Chris Canova
said.
   But defense attorney Greg Cummings called the case ``a great
injustice.''
   ``What really burns me is that the victim admits she was sexually
active ... In this case, we had a young girl who's not totally a
child. She knew what she was doing. She and Carlos had sex more than
once voluntarily. She told Carlos she was 15. And she was seen
having sex with other boys. This is not the little child the statute
was designed to protect.''
   But neither the jurors nor Judge Kevin Davey agreed.
   ``I think this business of teen-agers and children having
children is one of the biggest problems of our society, along with
the drug problem,'' Davey said.
   The girl, now a seventh-grader, testified Thursday that she and
Johnson had had sex and they had talked about it beforehand.
   Florida law says it doesn't matter whether a child consents.
Canova had to prove only that the victim was under 12 and sexual
intercourse occurred.
