<HEAD>10 Workers Die in Fire at Meat-Packing Plant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ten workers died of burns and
asphyxiation when a fire swept through a meat-packing plant in San
Antonio, police said Friday.
   Police and firemen said they are investigating conflicting
reports about the origin of the blaze Thursday night at a plant
owned by Paraguayan industrialist Roberto Antebi. San Antonio is 22
miles south of this capital.
   Officials said unconfirmed reports indicate the fire was caused
by an electrical short circuit or welders working near coolant pipes.
   The victims, at work when the fire broke out, were trapped by a
dense cloud of smoke and rapidly spreading flames, officials said.
