she was progressing well.
   ``Her heart is much better and her temperature is practically
normal,'' said one nun, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   Mother Teresa became ill Sunday night but insisted on attending
Mass on Monday. Her condition deteriorated and on Tuesday she was
admitted to the private hospital with a high fever and an irregular
heart beat.
   Born in Yugoslavia, she has traveled widely since winning the
Nobel Peace Prize in 1979.
   The order she founded now includes 3,000 nuns in 87 countries.
