<FIRST>u i AM-Panama-Protest     09-08 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Panama-Protest,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Panamian Soldiers Break Up Student Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Riot troopers firing tear gas on
Friday broke up a crowd of high school students protesting the
closing of two schools this week for anti-government activity,
witnesses said.
   Students trying to block streets near Remon Cantera School were
stopped by about 40 soldiers. The school is Panama's largest, with
about 4,000 students.
   No arrests or injuries were reported in the two-hour
demonstration.
   Remon Cantera was evacuated and Education Minister Juan Bosco
Bernal will decide whether to suspend classes, a ministry spokesman
said.
   The ministry earlier this week closed the National Institute
after firebombs were found there. Authorities said students planned
to throw them at police. It shut the American Institute after
anti-government demonstrations.
   Ministry officials say the ministry will close any schools where
anti-government demonstrations occur.
   Two schools closed last month, one in Panama City and one in
Colon, remain shut.
</TEXT>
