<FIRST>r w AM-DisabilitiesAct CORRECTIVE   09-08 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Disabilities Act, CORRECTIVE,0096</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: Members who used AM-Disabilities Act, versions of which were
sent as a0644, a0712, a0812, a0814, a0402, a0405 and a0427 on Sept. 7 for
AMs of Friday, Sept. 8 under a Washington dateline, are asked to use the
following story</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously
Thursday that the Americans with Disabilities Act which passed the
Senate would guarantee employment rights and other benefits to most
AIDS victims, and exclude those in an advanced, highly contagious
form of the disease.
   In fact, all AIDS victims are covered under the legislation.
</TEXT>
