<FIRST>r f PM-RJRSaleList     09-08 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-RJR Sale List,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-RJR-Del Monte, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here's a list of asset sales by RJR Nabisco Inc.
since it was acquired by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co. in a record
$25 billion buyout earlier this year:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _Five European food businesses, including two of Britain's
largest potato chip manufacturers, Walkers Crisps and Smiths Crisps,
to BSN S.A. of France for $2.5 billion. BSN later sold the chip
operations to Pepsico Inc. for $1.35 billion but said it planned to
keep the United Kingdom biscuit business of Nabisco Brands; The
Belin Group, a French biscuit and pastry business; and Saiwa, a
biscuit and snack producer in Italy.
   _The Chun King food division for $52 million to Singapore-based
Yeo Hiap Seng Limited and Fullerton Holdings Pte. Ltd., a subsidiary
of Temasek Holdings Pte. Ltd.
   _Associated Biscuits International Limited to Britannia
Industries Pte. Ltd. of Singapore for $44 million. ABIL, based in
England, owns about 38 percent of Britannia Industries in India and
40 percent of English Biscuit Manufacturers Ltd. in Pakistan.
   _The fresh fruit operations of Del Monte to the British
conglomerate Polly Peck International PLC for $875 million.
</TEXT>
