<TEXT>
   Share prices closed higher Friday on London's stock
exchange, but well below intraday peaks because of some late
profit-taking.
   The FT-SE 100-share index, the broadest measure of the market,
closed up 8 points, or 0.33 percent, at 2,423.9, but down from an
