by the Labor Department at 8:30 a.m.; merchandise trade for July by
the Commerce Department at 8:30 a.m.; industrial production and
capacity utilization for August by the Federal Reserve at 9:15 a.m.;
and business inventories by the Commerce Department at 10 a.m.
   NEW YORK _ Corporate raider and former Singer Co. chairman Paul
A. Bilzerian is to be sentenced for stock parking and other
securities law violations.
