<SECOND>BC-Newspapers Sold,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Mississippi Weeklies Sold to Illinois Chain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Illinois publishing chain has bought two
weekly newspapers in Mississippi, the Kosciusko Star-Herald and the
Pontotoc Progress.
   American Publishing Co. of West Frankfort, Ill., bought the
newspaper for an undisclosed price, the weeklies' owner, W.C.
Shoemaker of Kosciusko, said Thursday.
   Ricki Williams, administrative assistant to American's president,
L.J. Perrotto, said the papers would retain editorial independence,
their staffs would remain in place and the current editors would
become publishers.
   The Kosciusko newspaper has a circulation of about 9,000, while
the Pontotoc newspaper reaches about 7,500 readers.
   The acquisitions bring to 174 the number of newspapers owned by
the Illinois chain, Williams said.
